welcome_message_body: "Welcome to vibrant North Kensington! Known for its charming streets and lively atmosphere, we invite you to explore and immerse yourself in all this beautiful city has to offer. Enjoy your stay!"

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Montgomery County Airport serves all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Montgomery County Airport is exclusively for private and chartered flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport serves both domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A at Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport primarily serves American Airlines and its partner airlines.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B at Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport primarily serves Delta Air Lines and its partner airlines.

terminals.name: Concourse C
terminals.description: Concourse C at Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport primarily serves United Airlines and its partner airlines.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Tipton AAF Airport serves commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Military Terminal
terminals.description: The military terminal at Tipton AAF Airport is used for military operations and personnel.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport for passengers to use.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Washington Dulles International Airport houses most of the airport's amenities, including check-in counters, baggage claim, and a variety of shops and restaurants.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A at Washington Dulles International Airport primarily serves domestic flights operated by United Airlines.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B at Washington Dulles International Airport is primarily used for international flights, with airlines such as Air France, British Airways, and Lufthansa operating out of this terminal.

terminals.name: Concourse C
terminals.description: Concourse C at Washington Dulles International Airport serves a mix of domestic and international flights, including airlines such as American Airlines, Delta, and Emirates.

wifi.note: Free wifi is available throughout the airport, but it may require periodic reconnection.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse A
terminals.description: Concourse A at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse B
terminals.description: Concourse B at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse C
terminals.description: Concourse C at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Concourse D
terminals.description: Concourse D at Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport serves domestic and international flights.

wifi.note: Free Wi-Fi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Lee Airport handles all commercial flights and services.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Lee Airport is used for private and charter flights.

wifi.note: Free wifi is available throughout the airport.
